words: Okay. I have this son.
He is twenty-four years old, lives in Long Beach, just
graduated from Cal State Long Beach, still living with his high school buddies.
But um, one of his favorite things is NASCAR auto racing,
and I happen to like NASCAR, too. Yknow I, I happen to like the cart races
too, 'cause when I was young I used to hang out with the racecars, and yknow I sorta dropped all that
when I got married and my kids were growing up. And I just think it's amazing that my son has
picked up on that and said, yknow, "Hey I love NASCAR," and yknow, all this other stuff.
And so FOX Sports... they were showing a hockey game on TV...
and they said, um, "Enter our Daytona Day contest, send us an essay
on why you should have the ulti-ultimate
Daytona Day party." And so, um, he went ahead and wrote this
essay and, between you and me, he probably was hammered, but he wrote this
essay talking about how him and his buddies, yknow, treat... treat the first
day, opening day for NASCAR which is Daytona Day like a national holiday.
And, yknow, he just wrote this essay and they chose him
to have this party at his house. And they gave him a huge
flat screen TV great, big TV, we're talking like sixty inches.
And they gave him a six hundred dollar catered
menu... yknow, from whatever catering place he wanted, so he, he
lives in Long Beach so he had picked Lucille's. And then they gave him five hundred dollars
cash, it was supposed to be to cover the taxes, but he really used it to buy alcohol
and a plane ticket for his mother to fly down. So, I got this ticket, flew down
to Long Beach, um, he had me picked up at the airport by an Uber.
Um, he cooked me dinner the first night I was down there. It was great,
eating my favorite food, shrimp and asparagus. And the girlfriend was there and, yknow,
we played games and talked and visited. And then the next day was the race and
so the TV crew showed up at the house, and that was, that was really cool,
having, like, yknow, the lights and cameras and TV crew
there all day. And yknow, it was just fun. It was just the most fun weekend
I ever had in my life. And, um, that's that. Zeke's
